Program: Outlook
Title: Life for Judges in Afghanistan
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbrzh
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
The murder of Afghan judge Sheikh Mohammed and life for judges in Afghanistan now. Also, copyright piracy causing problems for flower growers in Sanremo, Italy. Malnutrition in the children of Dhaka, Bangladesh and South East Asia. Black ballet dancer Raven Wilkinson on dealing with racism and Ku Klux Klan in 1960s USA. Show less